column1: We love our dogs. They love to race.

column7: D E Kettlewell & N E Phillips

column1: BIG TIME DUSTY (2) - began awkwardly crowded and lost ground in to the bend made some ground in the latter stages.
BIGTIME SAM (3) - caught heels and lost momentum soon after the start clipped heels and ran wide in to the bend soon after ran on to heels again checking back was unable to make ground thereafter.

ALAMEIN STRYDA (4) - hampered for some strides from the jump when tightened and jostled losing momentum ran on to heels in to the bend and ran out wide losing more ground was unable to get in to contention thereafter.
BIGTIME LEO (5) - ran inwards from the jump and jostled with runner to his inner for some strides checked and lost a length or so on the top bend couldn't make ground on the leaders to the line.

column3: Wanganui Jockey Club Races 14th February C1/C2

column5: Owned/Raced by: G Ross & F Manclark
column7: Trained by: G Ross & S Voyce

column1: CLASSIC RAPPER (1) - away well was severely crowded and checked in to the first turn losing ground was unable to improve thereafter finishing in the rear at the line a veterinary examination and was found to have pain in the left triceps /deltoid area.

MOTHER'S TOUCH (2) - handy in to the first turn when severely crowded and checked settled midfield on the outer racing extremely wide in to and down the back straight could not make ground thereafter a veterinary examination found no abnormalities.

BIG TIME ODETTE (3) - fav- attempted to angle across in to the first bend and was almost dragged down from behind losing momentum and ground was unable to get back in to contention a veterinary examination found the dog to have pain in the left shoulder.
BIGTIME BAILEY (4) - racing in to the first turn was dictated inwards on to heels checking out wide losing ground ran outwards over heels when improving nearing the home turn losing ground.

BIGTIME BRONX (3) - settled midfield contacted in the hindquarters in to the bend when crossing to the rail improved to change ground over the leaders heels nearing the home turn came together with OPAWA FLASH short of the line and jostled for a couple of strides.
OPAWA FLASH (4) - away fair angled across between runners in to the bend to lead across the top bend jostled with runner to his outer for a couple of strides just short of the line.
PARIS END (6) - tightened jostled and checked in the early running settling back improved between runners across the top bend battled away in the run to the line.
FARE DODGER (7) - fav- hampered racing from the start when tightened and checked back he was forced to race widest in to and around the bend as he made good ground effort told in the latter stages.
SO SEVERE (8) - angled across from the jump causing tightening and checks to runners to her inner for some strides.

column5: Owned/Raced by: L Cole & C Rendle

column1: BIG TIME ABBI (1) - contact on jumping away checked wide over heels in to the first turn raced widest thereafter making ground along the back straight in to the far bend effort told in the run to the line.
BIG TIME ANTON (2) - contact with runner to his inner racing from the boxes settled back in to the first turn was able to improve towards the leaders around the bend in to the back straight
BIG TIME BABY (4) - crowded and checked in to the first turn was forced to check wide off hindquarters then hampered again soon after made ground in the run to the line.

KONGS OUT AGAIN (5) - fav- contact and went sideways for a stride or so in the run around the first turn losing some momentum and a couple of lengths did cover some extra ground in the running to the home straight.
BIGTIME ALFIE (6) - angled across in to the first turn causing tightening and jostling to several runners to his inner

BIGTIME DAISY (8) - angled across in to the first turn attempted to angled inwards across the face of BIGTIME ALFIE but was unable to being checked losing momentum and ground back to the rear was unable to get back in to contention thereafter.

FUNZALO (1) - bumped and checked inwards racing from the start checked outwards in to the bend causing interference to himself and several runners to his outer with him losing all chance from this point on.
GIRAFFE CLUB (2) - fav-settled midfield checked in to the bend losing momentum and a fair amount of ground no chance from there.
SEDGEBROOK LOVER (4) - severely crowded and checked in to the bend losing momentum and all chance from this point.
MILLIE PRINCE (7) - severely checked in to the bend losing momentum and all chance from this point.
IDOL DUKE (8) - severely checked in to the bend being forced extremely wide losing all chance from this point .

column5: Owned/Raced by: Upper Hutt Cossie and Company

column1: BIGTIME HONEY up 1.7 kgs today vetted clear to start.

ROWDY RUBY (2) - away ok dictated back and was tightened in making contact with the rail racing in to the bend losing ground was unable to get back in to contention a veterinary examination found no abnormalities.

BIG TIME LEBRON (3) - went up with the lids contact soon after the start dictated inwards across the face of ROWDY RUBY checking this runner settled midfield came together with BIGTIME LIZZY and jostled for a couple of strides ran outwards in to the home straight made some ground in the latter stages.
BIGTIME HONEY (4) - dwelt at the jump was unable to clear heels in the run to the bend racing out wide losing ground was unable to get in to contention thereafter.
BIGTIME LIZZY (5) - hampered when improving on the outer of BIG TIME LEBRON being jostled and forced out wide nearing the home turn losing ground finishing in the midfield at the line.

DYNAMITE DANGER (7) - ran inwards from the jump across the face of BIG TIME TINA and running in to BIGTIME LIZZY was then checked as he ran in to tight quarters in to the bend losing momentum and ground was unable to get back in to contention .

BIG TIME MAPLE (1) - began awkwardly being unbalanced for a stride or so contacted and went sideways for a stride or so when leading towards the back straight where he was crossed and checked losing momentum going back and was unable to improve thereafter.

BIG TIME ELSA (2) - began awkwardly and was unbalanced for a stride or so hampered in to the first turn when avoiding heels jostling with runner to her outer as she attempted to change ground was unbalanced again losing momentum and ground back to the rear was unable to improve thereafter.
BIGTIME ROD (3) - fav- contact and tightened in to the first turn caught heels soon after recovered stride quickly to lead in to the back straight strongest to the line.
BIGTIME BRUNO (4) - crowded and checked when racing in tight quarters racing in to the first turn went wide and was widest in to the back straight effort told in the run to the line
BIG TIME DYNASTY (5) - led in to the first turn bumped with runner to his inner and checked by improving runner losing momentum and ground finishing in the midfield at the line.
BIGTIME ACACIA (6) - hampered when tightened and checked racing in to the first turn going back towards the rear made good ground through the body of the field to the line.
BIG TIME SETH (8) - hampered racing in to the first turn when avoiding heels was then able to angle to the rail made good ground thereafter to the line.
IDOL PATCHES (1) - contact soon after the start checked soon after losing momentum back towards the rear was unable to improve thereafter.
SIR DUGGIE (2) - fav- hampered in to the bend when crossed losing momentum and a length or so.

ZARA CHEEBEE (3) - ran inwards from the jump bumping with IDOL PATCHES soon after was jostled and checked out across heels becoming unbalanced for a couple of strides losing momentum was unable to get back in to contention
BIGTIME BANJO (4) - hampered soon after the start when racing in tight quarters being checked and going back in to the bend racing out wide was unable to get back in to contention.

column3: Accell "Leading The Way In Canine Therapy" C4/C5

column1: BIG TIME IZZY (1) - angled outwards in to the first turn contacting and forcing BIG TIME SPOT wider.

BIGTIME BENJI (2) - jumped away well checked and lost momentum in to the first turn was unable to make ground thereafter finishing a margin in the rear at the line a veterinary examination that the dog had cramped up with pain also in the left hip abductors
BIG TIME SPOT (7) - contact and pushed outwards in to the first turn losing several lengths.
BIG TIME KOBE (8) - angled across in to the first turn checking runner to his inner.

column7: D E Kettlewell & N E Phillips

column1: WATERLOO PINK (1) - began awkwardly running out sharply across the face of BELMONTS and in to ALAMEIN TANE resulting in WATERLOO PINK going sideways and then forced to straighten ran on to heels and checked in to the bend losing momentum and ground finishing towards the rear at the line a veterinary examination found to have pain in the left triceps.

BELMONTS (2) - fav- severely checked and fell at the start he quickly recovered to his paws to finish on to the lure some distance behind the field a veterinary examination found a tear to the left deltoid muscle
ALAMEIN TANE (3) - contact in the hindquarters racing from the start recovered quickly from this incident to race up handy clipped from behind in to the bend. only battled to the line.
SEDGEBROOK SAINT was a late scratching at kenneling on vets advice.
HASHTAG BLESSED (1) - improving in to the bend when running in to the hind of BIGTIME TOBY was able to quickly recover his stride and finished on.

BIGTIME TOBY (2) - jumped well followed the leader in to the bend when galloped on from behind and checked losing momentum and faltering finished a margin in the rear at the line a veterinary examination found a fracture to the right side hock area with the dog being euthanised.
BREED APART (6) - racing handy to the bend when checked and jostled from her outer for some strides losing ground recovered good ground to the line.
SEDGEBROOK SALLY (7) - angled across in to the bend hampering runners to her inner and causing herself to be checked for some strides losing ground was unable to get back in to contention thereafter.
COCKNEY RIP OFF (8) - widest when angling inwards in to the bend was bumped and ran wide losing ground and raced widest thereafter to the line.

OPAWA HENRY (1) - soon after the angled outwards and was checked losing momentum and ground back to a clear last in the running finishing a margin in the rear at the line a veterinary examination found the dog to have suffered a tear to the left deltoid.
CAWBOURNE MOSS (2) - hampered for some strides in the run to the bend when pressured for some strides by crossing runner.
BIG TIME LORNA (4) - hampered soon after the start when forced inwards and checked losing momentum and ground was unable to get back in to contention thereafter.

SOFTY BURGESS (6) - fav- only fairly away soon after angled across on to BIG TIME LORNA checking this runner and OPAWA HENRY to her inner SOFTY BURGESS settled back of midfield made some ground to the line.
TUFF JEWEL (7) - forced to race wide in to the bend.
